args:
Cleo and Mitsuba are out foraging when they
come upon a girl named Pecorine who has
somehow arrived from another world. The three
then decide to join forces and make for the
Memoria Caverns in order to solve the mystery
of how she came to their neck of the woods.
(...Where am I? Is this a dream?)
(It's so strange and unfamiliar...\nand yet it feels so WARM.)
Welcome to my world. Alas, I fear we are\nunder siege from the terrible influence\nof the creature known as Aether.
I am Lumière Pandora—and you, my dear,\nare the shining hope who has been chosen\nto defeat Aether.
Okay, so if any of this is supposed to\nmake sense, it actually doesn't. ...Ah!
Aether rises! I'm afraid we must\ncut our communication short.
My world is on the other side of this rift.\nJump in before it collapses!
Once you've arrived, head west and find\nthe caverns where memories gather.
...She's gone. Well, THAT sure was a thing.\nWeird.
Still, she really seems to need help,\nwhich means I've got work to do!

Cleo and Mitsuba are out foraging when they
come upon a girl named Pecorine who has
somehow arrived from another world. The three
then decide to join forces and make for the
Memoria Caverns in order to solve the mystery
of how she came to their neck of the woods.
Something good's bubbling in the pot...\nYou just wanna grab the lid,\nbut it's too dang hot... ♪
I've finished prepping the mushrooms\nand vegetables, Mitsuba.
And the rice is almost done, so let's toss\nin the butter and make an Alberian pilaf!
Lunch with fresh picked ingredients, is it?\nI suppose being on food-procurement duty\ndoes have its share of perks.
Whoa. I've never seen anyone eat rice that\nfast before—and I live with Ranzal.
Watching somebody go to town on your\nchow is what being a chef is all about!
YUMMY! I tell you, food really IS\nthe source of all life!
Your pilaf has snatched me from the cruel\njaws of death, good lady. Thank you!
Well, I suppose we are all in this together,\nyes? But if I may, who are you?
Oh, geez! I forgot to introduce myself!\nYou can call meeee...
Good to meet you, Pecorine.\nI am Cleo, and this is Mitsuba.
Cleo and Mitsuba, got it. Heyas! ☆
So what are you doing out here\nin the wilderness, Pecorine?
Oh, I was on my way back to Landosol\nafter some training in the wilderness and\nthought I'd camp for a bit.
But when I woke up, everything had\nchanged. I couldn't find the road again,\nand looking for it made me super hungry.
Pretty much, yeah. How crazy is that?! ☆
Anyway, can one of you lovely ladies tell\nme where in Astraea are we right now?
Sorry, did you mean GRASTAEA?\nBecause we're in the south of that.
Also, I have never heard of a place\ncalled Landosol before.
Ha ha ha! Oh, you guys! That's a good one.
Wait, you're serious. Uh oh.\nThen where the heck AM I?!
There's no continent called Astraea\nanywhere in the world, so far as I know.
Oh jeez... Maybe that dream WASN'T\na dream after all!
Er, maybe you should start from the\nbeginning of what happened to you?
....I see. So you jumped through the rift\nand ended up here.
That's pretty much the long and short\nof it, yup.
This Lumière Pandora person welcomed\nyou to ＂her world,＂ correct?
If that's the case, it means you've come\nhere from an entirely different world.
I dunno, Cleo. Seems like a stretch.

We've had some experience with this
sort of thing in the past. Also, the fact
she is unfamiliar with dragons only
leads credence to the theory.
Oh, I know all about dragons.\nThey're delicious!
Sure! The tails make an AMAZING stew.\nOh man, now I'm hungry again...
Okay, you're right—she's DEFINITELY\nfrom another world!
In our world, dragons are creatures that\nrule over nature and mana. No one here\nwould ever even think of eating one.
Huh. Guess I really AM in another world.\nHow crazy is that?! ☆
Okay, well, time to take this seriously.\nIf can't figure out how to get home,\nI'm gonna be in big trouble.
Based on what you said, that Lumière\nPandora girl should know something.
Well, you said you were called to this\nworld to defeat this ＂Aether＂ that's\nthreatening us, correct?
Yep. Oh, and she also told me to head for\ncaves to the west where memories gather.

They are places where mana accumulates.
In our world, when people die, it's said
their souls become mana and travel out
over the world.
The memories carried by those souls\nare said to gather at mana founts.
The only area west of here with a mana\nfount is the Memoria Caverns.
Okay, that's extremely helpful.\nI'll go check it out right away!
Hold on, now! The caverns are rather far\nfrom here, and you're bound to run into\nfiends along the way.
Oh don't worry about me.\nI'm a trained warrior!
Plus, that girl sounded like she was in \nserious trouble; I can't just abandon her.
Heh. Your attitude very much reminds me\nof {player_name}.
Well, if you're that determined to go,\nwe've no choice but to accompany you.
Of course! We can't just leave you to\nstumble around in some unfamiliar world.
Besides, if there is a crisis brewing,\nwe need to learn about it.
Still, this will likely be a perilous journey.\nWe should return to the castle and prepare\nas best we can.
Come, Pecorine. We'll show you the way\nback to the Halidom.
Oh man, you guys are the BEST!\nBring it in!
